title: m203
body:
An American single-shot, muzzle-loading [[40mm grenade|40mm]] [[underbarrel grenade launcher]]. It was designed to replace the [[M79]], which was a stand-alone weapon. The under-barrel design gave soldiers the advantage of having quicker switch of both [[rifle]] and [[grenade launcher]], making them more adaptable in combat. The M203 was originally designed designed for the [[M16]] and [[M4 Carbine]] but can be fitted to many other rifles without modification.

title: byerley_turk_(umamusume)
body:
In [i][[Umamusume]][/i], the Byerley Turk refers both to one of the Three Goddesses of the [i]Umamusume[/i] universe as well as a training AI based on her, who is one of the hosts of the Grand Masters scenario. She represents "Discipline" and is represented by the color yellow.

A [[horse girl]], she has short brown and black two-toned hair as well as purple eyes. She wears a yellow military-style outfit and has a scar across her left eye. Overall, she somewhat resembles [[Symboli Rudolf (umamusume)|]] (and not by coincidence, as described below). She has a crown-like accessory on [b]her right ear[/b].

She is based on the Byerley Turk, one of the foundation sires of the Thoroughbred breed of horses. His umamusume's military theme is based on the fact that the Byerley Turk was originally a war horse. Through Herod, he is the sire-line ancestor of about 4% of all Thoroughbreds. In the context of [i]Umamusume[/i], he is the real-life ancestor of only 6 characters: Those who are part of Partholon's sire-line ([[Symboli Rudolf (umamusume)|]], [[Tokai Teio (umamusume)|]], [[Tsurumaru Tsuyoshi (umamusume)|]], [[Samson Big (umamusume)|]] and [[Mejiro McQueen (umamusume)|]]) as well as [[Daitaku Helios (umamusume)|]].

h5. Associated characters
[[Darley Arabian (Umamusume)|]] - Fellow Goddess/Training AI
[[Godolphin Barb (Umamusume)|]] - Fellow Goddess/Training AI

In [i][[Umamusume]][/i], the Darley Arabian refers both to one of the Three Goddesses of the [i]Umamusume[/i] universe as well as a training AI based on her, who is one of the hosts of the Grand Masters scenario. She represents "Bravery" and is represented by the color red.

A [[horse girl]], she has long red hair with a white blaze marking as well as green eyes. She has distinctively [[dark skin]] and wears a summer casual outfit baring her shoulders. She has an accessory on [b]her right ear[/b].

She is based on the Darley Arabian, one of the foundation sires of the Thoroughbred breed of horses. Through Eclipse, he is the sire-line ancestor of 95% of all Thoroughbreds. In the context of [i]Umamusume[/i], he is the real-life sire-line ancestor of the vast majority of the cast.

title: karl_urban
body:
Karl-Heinz Urban (born 7 June 1972) is a [[New Zealand]] actor. His career began with appearances in New Zealand films and TV series such as [[Xena: Warrior Princess]]. His first Hollywood role was in the 2002 horror film Ghost Ship. Since then, he has starred in many high-profile movies, including as Éomer in the second and third installments of [[The Lord of the Rings]] trilogy, Vaako in the second and third installments of the Riddick film series, [[Leonard McCoy]] in the [[Star Trek]]  [[star trek: kelvin timeline|film reboot series]] and Skurge in [[Marvel|Marvel Studios']] [[Thor: Ragnarok]].

Since 2019, he has starred as [[Billy Butcher]] in Amazon's superhero streaming television series [[The Boys]].

title: seven_lucky_gods
body:
七福神 ([i]Shichi-Fuku-Jin[/i], lit. Seven Lucky Gods) are the seven gods of fortune in Japan. 

They originated from various mythologies of India and China. However, their myths and shapes are far different from their origins. 

They are often depicted on their ship, the 宝船 ([i]Takarabune[/i], lit. Treasure Ship). According to Japanese folklore, if you want to dream a lucky "[i]hatsuyume[/i],":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hatsuyume you shall put a picture of Takarabune under your pillow. 

[[Bishamonten]], [[Benzaiten (mythology)|]] and [[ebisu_(mythology)|Ebisu]] are often worshipped independently.

title: crow
body:
A large, all-black passerine [[bird]].

Scientifically, crows are one species of bird in the broader Corvidae family, which includes crows, ravens, rooks, jackdaws, jays, magpies, treepies, choughs, and nutcrackers. On Danbooru, "crow" includes all visually-similar birds in the Corvidae family.

Birds in the Corvidae family range in size from the relatively small pigeon-size jackdaws (Eurasian and Daurian) to the Common Raven of the Holarctic region and Thick-billed Raven of the highlands of Ethiopia. The 40 or so members of Corvus genus occur on all temperate continents (except South America) and several offshore and oceanic islands.

Crow species found in Japan, aside from [[magpie]]s, jays and nutcrackers, include the rook, [[carrion crow]], Eurasian & Daurian jackdaws, the large-billed crow, and the common raven.

[[Touhou]] characters [[Shameimaru Aya]] and [[Himekaidou Hatate]] are crow [[tengu]], while [[Reiuji Utsuho]] is a hell raven youkai.

title: white_castle
body: White Castle is an American regional hamburger restaurant chain with 345 locations across 13 states, with its greatest presence in the Midwest and New York metropolitan area. Founded on September 13, 1921, in Wichita, Kansas, it has been generally credited as the world's first fast-food hamburger chain. It is known for its small, square hamburgers referred to as "sliders". The burgers were initially priced at five cents until 1929 and remained at 10 cents until 1949. In the 1940s, White Castle periodically ran promotional ads in local newspapers which contained coupons offering five burgers for ten cents, takeout only. In 2014, Time named the White Castle slider "The Most Influential Burger of All Time".

title: second_battle_of_el_alamein
body:
[b]The Second Battle of El Alamein[/b] (23 October – 11 November 1942) was a battle of [[World War II]] that took place near the Egyptian railway halt of El Alamein. The [[First Battle of El Alamein]] and the [[Battle of Alam el Halfa]] had prevented the Axis from advancing further into [[Egypt]].

Lieutenant-General [[Bernard Montgomery]] was appointed Commander-in-chief of all allied forces in Africa and led the Eighth Army successful offensive during this battle on which he defeated the Axis forces of [[Erwin Rommel]].

The British [[victory]] was the beginning of the end of the Western Desert Campaign, eliminating the Axis [[Afrika Korps]] threat to Egypt, the Suez Canal and the Middle Eastern and Persian oil fields. The battle revived the morale of the Allies, being the first big success against the Axis since [[Operation Crusader]] in late 1941. The end of the battle coincided with the Allied invasion of French North Africa in [[Operation Torch]] on 8 November, which opened a second front in North Africa.

title: battle_of_leyte_gulf
body:
[b]The Battle of Leyte Gulf[/b] (Japanese: レイテ沖海戦, romanized: [i]Reite Oki Kaisen[/i], lit. [b]Leyte Open Sea Naval Battle[/b]) was the [b]largest naval battle of [[World War II]][/b] and by some criteria [b]the largest naval battle in history[/b], with over 200,000 naval personnel involved. It was fought in waters near the [[Philippines]] islands of Leyte, Samar, and Luzon from 23 to 26 October 1944 between combined [[united_states|American]] and [[Australia]]n forces and the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] (IJN), as part of the [b]Allied invasion of Leyte[/b], which aimed to isolate Japan from the colonies that it had occupied in Southeast Asia, a vital source of industrial and oil supplies.

By the time of the battle, [[Japan]] had much fewer capital ships ([[aircraft carrier]]s and [[battleship]]s) left than the Allied forces had total aircraft carriers in the Pacific, which underscored the disparity in force strength at that point in the war. Regardless, the IJN mobilized nearly all of its remaining major naval vessels in an attempt to defeat the Allied invasion, but it was repulsed by the US Navy's Third and Seventh Fleets.

The battle consisted of four main separate engagements (the Battle of the Sibuyan Sea, the Battle of Surigao Strait, the Battle off Cape Engaño, and the Battle off Samar), as well as lesser actions. Allied forces announced the end of organized Japanese resistance on the island at the end of December.

It was also the [b]first battle in which Japanese aircraft carried out organized [[kamikaze pilot]] attacks[/b] (which were deadly effective and sunk many Allied ships), and it was the [b]last naval battle between battleships in history[/b]. The battle ended in a decisive [[victory]] for the Allies. The Japanese Navy suffered heavy losses and never sailed in comparable force thereafter since it was stranded for lack of fuel in its bases for the rest of the war.

title: grand_theft_auto
body:
A series of sandbox open world action games published by Rockstar Games.

The first game in the series was released in 1997. The release of [[Grand Theft Auto III]] in 2001 catapulted the franchise to massive mainstream success, eventually becoming one of the best-selling videogame franchise of all time.

Each game is set in a fictional city loosely based on a real life city. The games usually center around a criminal climbing through the ranks of the criminal underworld, while committing crimes such as carjacking, robbery, drugs, prostitution, etc. All of these elements made the series controversial.

title: isokaze_(kancolle)
body:
"Seaside Wind"

Isokaze is the 12th ship of the Kagerou-class destroyers in [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i].

h4. Appearance
She has [[long_hair|long]] [[black hair]] with [[tress_ribbon|red tress ribbons]] and [[red eyes]]. Some art makes light on how she essentially looks like a black-haired [[murakumo (kancolle)|Murakumo]] and a pixiv tag is dedicated to how she looks like a tiny [[nagato (kancolle)|Nagato]].

She wears a [[long_sleeves|long-sleeved]] white and blue [[serafuku]] with a yellow scarf on top of the standard Kagerou-class [[pleated skirt]], [[white gloves]] & [[uneven legwear|socks of different lengths]]. She [[dual_wielding|dual wields]] two pistols, one based from a standard 12.7cm twin gun and another is a collection of AA guns. On her back is her rigging. Unlike her sisters, it was made into a style similar to some larger ships' split bow. On her right is the part corresponding to her sisters' rigging with an additional 12.7 gun and a quadruple torpedo launcher attached to it and to her left is a depth charge launcher with another torpedo launcher attached to it.

In her remodel, her scarf has been changed to a rope, her thighhigh gains a stripe, the Standard 12.7cm guns have been replaced by their High-Angle equivalent, a radar has been propped behind her head and finally, camo-textures are added to her uniform.

For her B remodel (which is [i]not[/i] an actual second remodel), she is essentially the same as in her remodel except for her use of long 10cm guns. While she is now significantly more powerful stats-wise, the portrait serves as an art refresher.

h4. Personality
Like Nagato, she has a straightforward and professional personality with great pride in her fighting abilities. Perhaps because of this, she prefers a frontal and aggressive approach in battle rather than to engage in defensive measures.

It is implied in her hourlies that she is the only one in her division with poor culinary skills. At 0700, she said that [[hamakaze (kancolle)|Hamakaze]] told her how to make breakfast for the admiral but it ended in failure. At 1200, Tanikaze made the rice balls they ate at that time. At 1800, she ends up cooking with Urakaze. At 2000, it is revealed Urakaze made custard while Isokaze made grilled fish. The next hourlie implies that Urakaze's dish was better than Isokaze's. This has been exaggerated to the point that, if she and [[hiei (kancolle)|Hiei]] are allowed to cook together, they will produce something that is multiplicatively worse than if the two are allowed to cook separately.

Due to her blunt personality, Isokaze is often depicted by fans as either being oblivious to her poor performance or simply being a narcisstic. Because of this, she is frequently depicted in ecchi/NSFW works as being more seasoned in sexual matters or simply viewing it as another form of competition. Alternatively, others have also depicted her in the more ladylike demeanour.

She is voiced by [[Kawasumi Ayako]], who also voices [[ooyodo (kancolle)|Ooyodo]], [[unryuu (kancolle)|Unryuu]], [[kamikaze (kancolle)|Kamikaze]] and the [[Midway Princess]]. Isokaze, in particular, shares a voice identical to [[Saber (fate)|]], who incidentally has much in common with her.

title: musashi_(battleship)
body:
[b]Musashi[/b] (武蔵), named after the former Japanese province, was one of four planned Yamato-class battleships built for the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] (IJN), beginning in the late 1930s. The [[yamato_(battleship)|Yamato-class ships]] were the heaviest and most powerfully armed battleships ever constructed, displacing almost 72,000 long tons (73,000 t) fully loaded and armed with nine 460-millimetre (18.1 in) main guns. Their secondary armament consisted of four 155-millimetre (6.1 in) triple-gun turrets formerly used by the Mogami-class cruisers. They were equipped with six or seven armed floatplanes to conduct reconnaissance.

Commissioned in mid-1942, Musashi was modified to serve as the flagship of the Kidou Butai (Combined Fleet) during [[World War II]], and spent the rest of the year working up. The ship was transferred to Truk, Japan's main wartime naval base in the South Pacific theatre, in early 1943 and sortied several times that year with the fleet in unsuccessful searches for American forces. She was used to transfer forces and equipment between Japan and various occupied islands several times in 1944. Torpedoed in early 1944 by an American submarine, Musashi was forced to return to Japan for repairs, during which the navy greatly augmented her anti-aircraft armament. 

She was present during the [[Battle of the Philippine Sea]] in June, but did not come in contact with American surface forces. During the [[Battle of Leyte Gulf]], Musashi was sunk by an estimated 19 torpedo and 17 bomb hits from American carrier-based aircraft on 24 October 1944. Over half of her crew was rescued. 

Her wreck was located in March 2015 by a team of researchers employed by [[Microsoft]] co-founder Paul Allen.

title: the_winged_dragon_of_ra
body:
A [[duel monster]] from [[yu-gi-oh!|Yu-Gi-Oh]], one of the 3 Egyptian God cards and the "leader" of the group.

Famous for its ridiculous amount of powerful effects it has in the [[Yu-gi-oh! duel monsters|anime]], with 22 in total. Ranging from being immune to almost all card effects, its effects being unnegateable, allows the user to destroy any card on the field by paying Life Points, can attack any monster that is summoned during the opponent's turn, allow the user to do "point-to-point" transfer by transferring their LP and the card's ATK/DEF back-and-forth as they wished, requires a specific "summoning chant" to be successfully summoned, and much more.

Due to this, when the [[real life]] version of the card were released in 2010, it was heavily downgraded to have a handful amount of effects. After more powerful monsters made their debut and the game's power ceiling has been steadily risen over the year, [[Konami]] later introduced a large number of support cards to emulate Ra's anime effects.

English name: The Winged Dragon of Ra
Japanese name: The Winged Divine Dragon of Ra

title: kino_(kino_no_tabi)

Kino is a composed, stoic, and precocious teenager who travels with her talking motorrad, [[Hermes (kino no tabi)|]]; the two have a contract—Kino provides the balance, Hermes provides the speed, and together they can travel anywhere they wish.  Although Kino appears apathetic at first, she is a caring and understanding person. She travels through different countries to experience their customs and understand their histories, but she never stays longer than three days, as she is afraid of settling down, and would thus cease being a traveler.

Kino is portrayed with either [[short_hair|short]] [[green hair]] and [[green eyes]] or [[black hair]] and [[black eyes]]. She wears a [[black jacket]], [[brown coat]], [[white shirt]], [[goggles on headwear|goggled cap]] and wide [[belt]] with lots of [[pouch]]es — using special gear depending on the weather or season as necessary, she is typically armed with a [[Colt 1851 Navy]] [[revolver]].

Due to her [[androgynous]] appearance, her gender is often confused by both viewers and other characters in the series.

title: battle_of_berlin
body:
[b]The Battle of Berlin[/b], designated as [b]the Berlin Strategic Offensive Operation[/b] by the [[Soviet Union]], and also known as [b]the Fall of Berlin[/b], was one of the last major offensives of the European theatre of [[World War II]].

After the Vistula–Oder offensive of January–February 1945, the [[Soviet Army]] had temporarily halted on a line 60 km (37 mi) east of Berlin. On March 9th, Germany established its defence plan for the city with Operation Clausewitz. The first defensive preparations at the outskirts of Berlin were made on March 20th, under the newly appointed commander of Army Group Vistula, "General Gotthard Heinrici":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gotthard_Heinrici .

When the Soviet offensive resumed on April 16th, two Soviet fronts (army groups) attacked Berlin from the east and south, while a third overran German forces positioned north of Berlin. Before the main battle in Berlin commenced, the Red Army encircled the city after successful (but very costly) battles of the Seelow Heights and Halbe. 

On April 20th, 1945, [[Adolf Hitler]]'s birthday, the 1st Belorussian Front led by "Marshal Georgy Zhukov":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georgy_Zhukov , advancing from the east and north, started shelling Berlin's city centre, while Marshal Ivan Konev's 1st Ukrainian Front broke through Army Group Centre and advanced towards the southern suburbs of Berlin. On April 23th General Helmuth Weidling assumed command of the forces within Berlin. The garrison consisted of several depleted and disorganised Army and Waffen-SS divisions, along with poorly trained Volkssturm and Hitler Youth members. Over the course of the next week, the Red Army gradually took the entire city.

On April 30th, Hitler and several of his officials committed suicide. The city of [[Berlin]]'s garrison surrendered on May 2nd but fighting continued to the north-west, west, and south-west of the city until the end of the war in Europe on May 8th (May 9th in the Soviet Union) as some German units fought westward so that they could surrender to the Western Allies rather than to the Soviets.

title: shinano_(aircraft_carrier)
body:
[b]Shinano[/b] was an [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] [[aircraft carrier]] during [[World War II]].

Originally laid down as the third [[Yamato_(battleship)|Yamato-class]] battleship, after the losses suffered at the [[Battle of Midway]] her half-completed hull was converted into an aircraft carrier. Construction was expedited after further losses during the Battle of the Philippine Sea, and Shinano was launched on October, 8th 1944 at Yokosuka Naval Arsenal. She was commissioned on November 19th, and dispatched nine days later to Kure Naval Base to complete her fitting out. En-route Shinano was torpedoed by American submarine USS Archerfish, and because much of her water-tight fixtures and damages-control equipment was not operational, she flooded and sank on November 29th, 1944. Shinano remains the largest warship to be sunk by a submarine.

title: a6m_zero
body:
The [b]Mitsubishi A6M[/b] was the primary carrier-based fighter aircraft operated by the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] during [[World War II]]. Its long designation was "Type 0 Carrier Fighter" (零式艦上戦闘機), and it was commonly called "Reisen" (零戦, zero fighter) by its pilots. This nickname was also popular among the Allies, more so than the official reporting name "Zeke". The plane was designed by [[Horikoshi Jirou]]. 

When the [b]ZERO[/b] was first introduced in 1940 it was considered the most capable carrier-based fighter, combining excellent maneuverability with a good climb rate and a very long operational range. These qualities combined with the excellent training of IJN pilots allowed the Japanese to win numerous early victories over their Allied adversaries. Because of its attributes the Zero was instrumental in the success of the attack at [[Pearl Harbor]].

However, after the Americans introduced the [[F6F Hellcat]] and [[F4U Corsair]] in 1942, both of which are much faster, have longer operational range, and are more resilient and have better armor than the Zero, it began to struggle to compete against both planes, particularly due to its weak airframe and being particularily vulnerable to boom-and-zoom tactics. In the later half of the war, with [[battle_of_midway|the loss of experienced IJN pilots]], the Zero were mostly assigned as suicidal [i][[kamikaze pilot|kamikaze]][/i] aircraft in a desperate attempt to defend the country of [[Japan]].

title: brutalizer
body: Also known as the [I]Scissored Armbar Crossface[/I], [I]Double Underhook Crossface[/I], or the [I]Double Arm Crossface[/I], it is a variation of the [[crippler crossface]] that is innovated by [[New Japan Pro Wrestling]] wrestler Nagata Yuuji as the [I]Nagata Lock III[/I]. It is a scissored armbar combined with a crossface, where the attacking wrestler traps one of the prone opponent's arms in his/her legs, wraps the opponent's other arm under the attacker's shoulder, and then applies the crossface. It is popularized in the present time by [[All Elite Wrestling]] wrestler Pac as the [I]Brutalizer[/I]. Other known users of this hold includes former professional wrestler [[Dave Bautista|Batista]] (who calls his version as the [I]Batista Bite[/I]), WWE wrestler Tommaso Ciampa (as the [I]Sicilian Stretch[/I]), All Elite Wrestling wrestlers Julia Hart (who uses a sitting variant which she calls as the [I]Hartless[/I]), and Dr. Britt Baker D.M.D. (who uses a combination with a Mandible Claw which she calls as the [I]Lockjaw[/I]).
